from nabil nabil ayoub subject re monophysite and mike walker in article d andrew byler write nabil ayoub write a a final note the oriental orthodox and eastren orthodox do sign a common statement of christology in which the heresey of monophysitism wa condemn so the coptic orthodox church do not believe in monophysitism sorry what do the coptic church believe about the will and energy of christ were there one or be there two human and divine will and energy in him also what be the objection ot the copt with the pope of rome why be there a coptic catholic church do you reject the supreme jurisdiction of the sucessor of st peter who bless st john mark bishop of alexandrium wa translator for and hi predecessor or hi infallibility or what other thing perhap for ymy first set of question regard the energy and will of christ i quote to you the relevant part of the statement sign by both eastern chalcedonian and oriental non-chalcedonian orthodox scholar a few year ago both family both orthodox church both family agree in condemn the eutychian heresy both family confes that the logo the second person of the holy trinity only beget of the father before the age and consubstantial with him wa incarnate and wa bear from the virgin mary theotoko fully consubstantial with u perfect man with soul body and mind nu o upsilon zetum he wa crucify die wa bury and rise from the dead on the third day ascend to the heavenly father where he sit on the right hand of the father a lord of all creation at pentecost by the come of the holy spirit he manifest the church a hi body we look forward to hi come again in the fullnes of hi glory accord to the scripture both family condemn the nestorian heresy and the crypto-nestorianism of theodoret of cyru they agree that it be not sufficient merely to say that christ be consubstantial both with hi father and with u by nature god and by nature man it be necessary to affirm also that the logo who be by nature god become by nature man by hi incarnation in the fullnes of time both family agree that the hypostasi of the logo become composite by unite to hi divine uncreated nature with it natural will and energy which he ha in common with the father and the holy spirit create human nature which he assume at the incarnation and make hi own with it natural will and energy both family agree that the nature with their proper energy and will be unite hypostatically and naturally without confusion without change without division and without separation and that they be distinguish in think alone both family agree that he who will and act be alway the one hypostasi of the logo incarnate i gues that adress ymy question adequately a for ymy second set of question i be afraid they be irrelevant to the discussion at least from my point of view of monophysitism i do not see how they relate to the topic we be discuss other than to start an endles orthodox-rc debate which i do not plan to engage into a a brief answer to ymy question the position of the coptic orthodox church regard the roman pontiff hi jurisdiction hi infalability etc be exactly the same a all the other orthodox church peace nabil nabil ayoub engine research center dept of mechanical engineering university of wisconsin-madison email ayoub 